  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kismayo and Baidoa Urban Water Supply and Sanitation Project - Additional Financing</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Both Kismayo and Baidoa have seen a rapid increase of returnees and internally displaced persons (IDPs) due to insecurity, drought, flooding and pursuit for better basic services and economic opportunities in Somalia. IDPs and returnees account for almost 60 per cent of the resident population in the two towns. The scale-up of this project will better serve and accommodate the influx of IDPs (who become permanent residents), estimated at 280,000 additional beneficiaries, in Kismayo and Baidoa and optimise benefits through the implementation of expanded activities to maximize the development impact of the water and sanitation sector in the two towns. The proposed modified designs would deliver water from the respective identified sources to the towns of Kismayo and Baidoa including the peri-urban areas and provide clean water to the IDPs and returnees in the two towns, thereby maximizing the development impact.</narrative>
  </description>
